    "stat_block": {
        "type": "stat_block",
        "subtype": "equipment",
        "text": "Worn on a necklace, this intricate key grants you greater facility with constructs. The key alerts you to constructs lurking around you. Whether or not you are Investigating, the GM automatically rolls secret Recall Knowledge checks for you when you see a construct pretending to be a normal object, statue, or the like. Typically, this check is Arcana, Crafting, or an appropriate Lore skill. On a success, you recognize the presence of the construct and gain the usual benefits of Recall Knowledge.  \n  \n While you're wearing the key, if your attack reduces a construct to 0 Hit Points, instead of destroying it completely, you can send it into a dormant state, from which you can study its inner workings and possibly (at the GM's discretion) spend time and money to reprogram or repurpose it. Even if you don't subvert it, you can Repair a construct rendered dormant this way, allowing you to return tomb guardians to their vigil after you've battled them. Additionally, you can activate the key in two ways to call a construct to serve you.",
        "level": 8,
        "traits": [
            {
                "name": "Uncommon",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 159,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 11",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 11",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 11,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "f31704572455b8d77a8bd97c0045fde6",
                "text": "Something of uncommon rarity requires special training or comes from a particular culture or part of the world. Some character choices give access to uncommon options, and the GM can choose to allow access for anyone. Less is known about uncommon creatures than common creatures. They typically can't be summoned. The DC of Recall Knowledge checks related to these creature is increased by 2.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Recall Knowledge",
                        "alt": "Recall Knowledge",
                        "game-obj": "Actions",
                        "aonid": 26
                    }
                ],
                "classes": [
                    "uncommon"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Conjuration",
                "type": "trait",
                "edition": "legacy",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Core Rulebook",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Core Rulebook pg. 630",
                            "alt": "Core Rulebook pg. 630",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 1
                        },
                        "page": 630,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "4.0",
                            "alt": "4.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 1
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "9011037bb4a11ca6cf2d16fa8a657bf5",
                "text": "Effects and magic items with this trait are associated with the conjuration school of magic, typically involving summoning, creation, teleportation, or moving things from place to place.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "summoning",
                        "alt": "summoning",
                        "game-obj": "Traits",
                        "aonid": 154
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "teleportation",
                        "alt": "teleportation",
                        "game-obj": "Traits",
                        "aonid": 156
                    }
                ],
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Invested",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 98,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "GM Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "GM Core pg. 219",
                            "alt": "GM Core pg. 219",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 218
                        },
                        "page": 219,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 218
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "56b56ea5f9d865dc549f0ed7372ab504",
                "text": "A character can invest only 10 magical items that have the invested trait. None of the magical effects of the item apply if the character hasn\u2019t invested it, nor can it be activated, though the character still gains any normal benefits from wearing the physical item (like a hat keeping rain off their head).",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "invest",
                        "alt": "invest",
                        "game-obj": "Actions",
                        "aonid": 2799
                    }
                ],
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Magical",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 103,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 458",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 458",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 458,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "15e2d048ce93e7b648064b09972535bc",
                "text": "Something with the magical trait is imbued with magical energies not tied to a specific tradition of magic. Some items or effects are closely tied to a particular tradition of magic. In these cases, the item has the arcane, divine, occult, or primal trait instead of the magical trait. Any of these traits indicate that the item is magical.",
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Transmutation",
                "type": "trait",
                "edition": "legacy",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Core Rulebook",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Core Rulebook pg. 637",
                            "alt": "Core Rulebook pg. 637",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 1
                        },
                        "page": 637,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "4.0",
                            "alt": "4.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 1
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "e15261ef9d67eae23579ccf106d27c86",
                "text": "Effects and magic items with this trait are associated with the transmutation school of magic, typically changing something\u2019s form.",
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            }
        ],
